<statement>
<p>Temperature change with respect to altitude can be modeled as</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{T}={15.04}^{\circ}\ \text{ C }\ -\frac{{{0.00649}^{\circ}\ \text{ C}}}{{{1}\ \text{ m}}}{h}</m></p>
<p>
  where</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{T}</m> is the resulting temperature.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{h}</m> is the altitude mean sea level.</p>
<p>This is a linear model.</p>
<p>
  What is the shift (y-intercept)? <fillin characters="7" /></p>
<p>
  What is the ratio (slope)? <fillin characters="7" /></p>
<p>
  What are the units for <m>\displaystyle{h}</m>? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>Celsius</li> 
<li>Celsius per meter</li> 
<li>meters</li> 
<li>meters per Celsius</li> 
</ol></p>
<p>
  What are the units for <m>\displaystyle{T}</m>? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>meters per Celsius</li> 
<li>Celsius</li> 
<li>meters</li> 
<li>Celsius per meter</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>15.04</li><li>-0.00649</li><li>C: meters</li><li>B: Celsius</li></ul></p>
</solution>
</myopenmath>

